<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 17 at 1:03PM CST  by NWS QuadCities</headline>
<description>...Heavy Snow Spreading into the Area
Periods of moderate to heavy snow are spreading into Henry County
Iowa this afternoon resulting in snowfall accumulations of less
than an inch. The heavy snow combined with northerly winds of 20
to 30 MPH will reduce visibility to near zero at times. Quick snow
accumulations will cause slick traveling conditions on area
roadways. Conditions will begin to improve after 3 PM as lighter
snow spreads into the area.
It traveling early this afternoon, be sure to slow down and allow
extra time to reach your destination.</description>
